      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1372: Removing the unconditional SwarmMessageUpdated emission makes normal edit updates disappear whenever plugins are disabled or no chat handlers are registered. The replacement signal is only emitted inside the ENABLE_PLUGIN/hasHandlers() path in announce(), so clients will not be notified that a message body changed in the common no-plugin case. Keep the base edit notification independent of plugin processing, and only add overwrite injection when plugin data is available.\n```suggestion\nlibjami::SwarmMessage updated \u003d *it-\u003esecond;\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\nupdated \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(*it-\u003esecond, history.quickAccess);\n#endif\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmMessageUpdated\u003e(accountId_, repository_-\u003eid(), updated);\n```",
      "revId": "6cf0f7e1ea8bad00a01b8ec3a5f53b76088e19db",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
